title: 820-00923 20V - 160mA no boot
message:
Hello everyone.

Got an 820-00923 for repair and can not find out how to fix it, without water damage
PPbus_g3H 13V
ALL_SYS_PWRGD 3.3V
3V3_S5 3.3V
3V3_SUS 3.3V
L7270 1.04V 
PM_PWRBTN_L 3.3V
PM_SLP_S3_L 3.3V
PM_SLP_S4_L 3.3V
pp1V8_s0 1.8V
PPVCC_S0_CPU 0V
PLT_RST_L 0V
PPVCC_S0_CPU 0V
PPVCCIO_S0_CPU 0.950V

what can it be?

title: 820-00923 20V - 160mA no boot
message:
Compare diode mode readings on CPU coils with good board.
Try known good BIOS...

title: 820-00923 20V - 160mA no boot
message:
Tried 3 BIOS and also to replace the BIOS chip, no success. 
I miss a working 820-00923 motherboard...
Something else I can try?

title: 820-00923 20V - 160mA no boot
message:
As you get VCCSA (L7270), I don't see other reason than bad CPU; if BIOS is good for sure.
Just in case, check all resistors and traces around U7100.
CPU_VR_EN_R is present?

title: 820-00923 20V - 160mA no boot
message: CPU_VR_EN_R present. Gave it back... I think CPU was dead too.
